These are Puzzles for 2x4 Level 7

.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-7-1::.
There are 4 different nationalities: spanish, polish, italian, british
The people's birthday is in 4 different months: january, june, march, july
1. the polish is between the spanish and the person who's birthday is in june##2
2. the polish is on the left or right of the person who's birthday is in january##3
3. the polish is somewhere between the british and the spanish##7
4. the person who's birthday is in june is in an even position##4
5. the british is on the right of the person who's birthday is in march##1
6. the person who's birthday is in june is somewhere to the left of the person who's birthday is in january##5

.:: Answer ::.
|            |    1    |     2     |       3       |      4      |
| Nationality   | italian | british       | polish | spanish        |
| Birthday      | march  | june | july        | january |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-7-2::.
The people have 4 different jobs:  musician, police-officer, dancer, videographer
City: miami, marseilles, hannover, paris
1. the person traveling to paris is somewhere between the person traveling to hannover and the dancer##7
2. the videographer is somewhere to the left of the musician##5
3. the videographer is somewhere to the right of the person traveling to paris##5
4. the police-officer is on the left of the videographer##1
5. the person traveling to paris is between the person traveling to hannover and the person traveling to marseilles##2

.:: Answer ::.
|         |    1     |     2      |       3       |    4    |
| Job     | dancer | police-officer       | videographer         | musician     |
| City   | marseilles   | paris | hannover | miami |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-7-3::.
4 different games are played: monopoly, go, billiard, snooker
The people have 4 different hobbies: baking, reading, board-games, card-games
1. the person playing monopoly is on the right of the person who's hobby is card-games##1
2. the person who's hobby is card-games is somewhere between the person who's hobby is reading and the person who's hobby is baking##7
3. the person who's hobby is board-games is on the left of the person playing snooker##1
4. the person who's hobby is baking is somewhere between the person who's hobby is card-games and the person playing go##7

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1   |     2      |    3    |    4    |
| Game   | go | snooker | billiard | monopoly  |
| Hobby   | board-games | baking  | card-games   | reading |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-7-4::.
There are 4 different favourite beverages: almond-milk, juice, water, fanta
There are 4 different favourite colors: coral, ivory, emerald, purple
1. the person who likes purple is on the far left or far right##3
2. the person drinking almond-milk is somewhere between the person who likes ivory and the person drinking fanta##7
3. the person drinking water is the person who likes purple##1
4. the person who likes emerald is on the left of the person who likes purple##1
5. the person drinking juice is on the left of the person who likes coral##1

.:: Answer ::.
|         |     1     |     2      |       3       |      4      |
| Beverage   | juice | almond-milk | fanta       | water |
| Color   | ivory      | coral   | emerald | purple  |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-7-5::.
The people have 4 different jobs:  social-worker, project-manager, analyst, mechanic
4 different brands of cigars are smoked: montecristo, davidoff, swisher, bolivar
1. the bolivar-smoker is on the left or right of the project-manager##3
2. the montecristo-smoker is somewhere to the left of the davidoff-smoker##5
3. the social-worker is on the right of the analyst##1
4. the bolivar-smoker is somewhere between the project-manager and the social-worker##7
5. the bolivar-smoker is on the left of the swisher-smoker##1
6. the davidoff-smoker is somewhere to the left of the bolivar-smoker##5
7. the project-manager is on the far left or far right##3
8. the social-worker is on the left or right of the analyst##3

.:: Answer ::.
|               |       1       |     2     |      3      |    4    |
| Job         | analyst | social-worker   | mechanic | project-manager |
| Cigar   | montecristo      | davidoff | bolivar      | swisher |

